# Code Standards

## One reason to exist

One responsibility per function, component, and file. Avoid god components/services, deep nesting, magic numbers, hidden side effects.

## Naming

Match the repo. Typical Hakimo Next conventions:

- `createXAction` / `updateXAction`
- `x.service.ts`, `x.repository.ts`, `x-page.tsx`, `x-form-dialog.tsx`
- Path alias `@/` → `src/`

## Types

TypeScript strictness as configured. Prefer explicit domain types over `any`. Parse external input with Zod.

## Reuse

Before creating a component/hook/util/service: search the codebase. Extend existing patterns.

## Errors

User-facing messages in the product language (usually Arabic). Log technical detail server-side. Prefer typed result unions (`{ ok: true|false }`) or consistent throw+toast patterns already used in the module.
